---
By: Gautama Buddha
Locus:
  Page: 81
  Verse: 8
Tags:
  - Death
---
Death If you ask, does a man live beyond death, I answer No, not in any
sense comprehensible to the mind of man which itself dies at death, and if
you ask, does a man altogether die at death, I answer No, for what dies is
what belongs to this world of form and illusion.
